---
// AssuranceTiers.astro
// Trust and Execution Lanes — comparison table + lane descriptions
---

<section class="section section--alt reveal" id="assurance">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="tiers">
      <h2 class="tiers__title">Trust and Execution Lanes</h2>
      <p class="tiers__intro text-secondary">
        The protocol is the same across lanes. What changes is who can see
        plaintext during execution and how much of the execution context can be
        verified afterwards.
      </p>

      <div class="tiers__scroll">
        <div class="tiers__table" role="table" aria-label="Comparison of execution lanes">
          <div class="tiers__row tiers__row--header" role="row">
            <div class="tiers__cell tiers__cell--label" role="columnheader"></div>
            <div class="tiers__cell tiers__cell--col" role="columnheader">
              <span class="tiers__col-name font-mono">Software</span>
            </div>
            <div class="tiers__cell tiers__cell--col" role="columnheader">
              <span class="tiers__col-name font-mono">TEE</span>
            </div>
            <div class="tiers__cell tiers__cell--col" role="columnheader">
              <span class="tiers__col-name font-mono">VCAV</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="tiers__row" role="row">
            <div class="tiers__cell tiers__cell--label" role="rowheader">
              <span class="font-mono">Counterparty sees raw input</span>
            </div>
            <div class="tiers__cell" role="cell"><span class="tiers__value tiers__value--good">No</span></div>
            <div class="tiers__cell" role="cell"><span class="tiers__value tiers__value--good">No</span></div>
            <div class="tiers__cell" role="cell"><span class="tiers__value tiers__value--good">No</span></div>
          </div>

          <div class="tiers__row" role="row">
            <div class="tiers__cell tiers__cell--label" role="rowheader">
              <span class="font-mono">Relay operator sees plaintext</span>
            </div>
            <div class="tiers__cell" role="cell"><span class="tiers__value tiers__value--warn">Yes</span></div>
            <div class="tiers__cell" role="cell"><span class="tiers__value tiers__value--good">No</span></div>
            <div class="tiers__cell" role="cell"><span class="tiers__value tiers__value--good">No</span></div>
          </div>

          <div class="tiers__row" role="row">
            <div class="tiers__cell tiers__cell--label" role="rowheader">
              <span class="font-mono">External model provider sees prompt</span>
            </div>
            <div class="tiers__cell" role="cell"><span class="tiers__value tiers__value--warn">Yes</span></div>
            <div class="tiers__cell" role="cell"><span class="tiers__value tiers__value--warn">Yes</span></div>
            <div class="tiers__cell" role="cell">
              <span class="tiers__value tiers__value--good">No</span>
              <span class="tiers__detail">planned local models</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="tiers__row" role="row">
            <div class="tiers__cell tiers__cell--label" role="rowheader">
              <span class="font-mono">Receipt coverage</span>
            </div>
            <div class="tiers__cell" role="cell">
              <span class="tiers__detail">Contract, schema, output</span>
            </div>
            <div class="tiers__cell" role="cell">
              <span class="tiers__detail">Plus attestation-bound execution evidence</span>
            </div>
            <div class="tiers__cell" role="cell">
              <span class="tiers__detail">Plus stronger execution and policy enforcement claims</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="tiers__row" role="row">
            <div class="tiers__cell tiers__cell--label" role="rowheader">
              <span class="font-mono">Hardware attestation</span>
            </div>
            <div class="tiers__cell" role="cell"><span class="tiers__value tiers__value--dim">No</span></div>
            <div class="tiers__cell" role="cell"><span class="tiers__value tiers__value--good">Yes</span></div>
            <div class="tiers__cell" role="cell"><span class="tiers__value tiers__value--good">Yes</span></div>
          </div>

          <div class="tiers__row tiers__row--last" role="row">
            <div class="tiers__cell tiers__cell--label" role="rowheader">
              <span class="font-mono">Status</span>
            </div>
            <div class="tiers__cell" role="cell">
              <span class="tiers__status tiers__status--available font-mono">Available</span>
            </div>
            <div class="tiers__cell" role="cell">
              <span class="tiers__status tiers__status--progress font-mono">Hardware validated</span>
            </div>
            <div class="tiers__cell" role="cell">
              <span class="tiers__status tiers__status--planned font-mono">In development</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tiers__descriptions">
        <div class="tier-desc">
          <h3 class="tier-desc__title font-mono">Software</h3>
          <p class="tier-desc__text text-secondary">
            The relay operator is trusted, as with a normal SaaS system. The
            protocol still constrains output and produces receipts.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="tier-desc">
          <h3 class="tier-desc__title font-mono">TEE</h3>
          <p class="tier-desc__text text-secondary">
            Execution runs inside hardware-isolated memory. The operator is
            excluded from plaintext visibility, though an external model provider
            may still see prompts if the model is called by API.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="tier-desc">
          <h3 class="tier-desc__title font-mono">VCAV</h3>
          <p class="tier-desc__text text-secondary">
            The highest-assurance tier. VCAV is designed to go further with local
            models, hardware attestation, and stronger containment of residual
            disclosure channels.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .tiers {
    max-width: var(--content-max);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .tiers__title {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .tiers__intro {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  }

  .tiers__scroll {
    overflow-x: auto;
    -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .tiers__table {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(160px, 220px) 1fr 1fr 1fr;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
    min-width: 600px;
  }

  .tiers__row {
    display: contents;
  }

  .tiers__row--header .tiers__cell {
    background: var(--color-bg-elevated);
    padding: var(--space-md);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .tiers__cell {
    padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);
    background: var(--color-bg-panel);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2px;
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
  }

  .tiers__row--last .tiers__cell {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .tiers__cell--label {
    background: var(--color-bg-elevated);
    border-right: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .tiers__col-name {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .tiers__value--warn {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--color-warning);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .tiers__value--good {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--color-success);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .tiers__value--dim {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .tiers__detail {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
    line-height: var(--leading-normal);
  }

  .tiers__status {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    padding: 0.15em 0.5em;
    border-radius: 3px;
    display: inline-block;
    width: fit-content;
  }

  .tiers__status--available {
    color: var(--color-success);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-success);
    opacity: 0.9;
  }

  .tiers__status--progress {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-accent-dim);
  }

  .tiers__status--planned {
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .tiers__descriptions {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .tier-desc__title {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .tier-desc__text {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  }

  @media (max-width: 639px) {
    .tiers__descriptions {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
